***(ID)                            JES2B603
***(SUBSYSTEM)                     JES2
***(DESIGNER)                      D.A.MOORCROFT
***(AUTHOR)
*
***(DATE WRITTEN)
***(DATE TESTED)
***(DATE INSTALLED)
*
***(ABSTRACT)
*
*        ADD THE COMMAND
*              $DX
*         TO PRODUCE A SUMMARY OF JOB STATUS.  THE OUTPUT COMPRISES
*         6 LINES OF INFORMATION, THUS:
*              HSPB603 NNN JOBS BUSY
*              HSPB603 NNN JOBS AWAITING EXEC
*              HSPB603 NNN JOBS AWAITING OUTPUT
*              HSPB603 NNN JOBS ON TAPE
*              HSPB603 NNN JOBS TOTAL
*              HSPB603 NNN % SPOOL
*
*        ( UNDER HASP 3.1 THIS WAS MODIFICATION 'M088' ).
*
***(LOGIC SUMMARY)
*
*        WITHIN THE AUXILIARY COMMAND PROCESSOR ( SEE JES2B002 ), INTERCEPT
*         COMMANDS OF THE FORM '$DX', ANALYSE THE JOB QUEUE AND PRODUCE THE
*         STATUS SUMMARY.  BEFORE RETURNING, SET THE COND CODE IN THE
*         PSW TO EQUALITY SO THAT JES2 PROCESSING WILL BE BYPASSED.
*
***(INSTALLATION)
*
*        ***** DESCRIBE INSTALLATION OR REFER TO ANOTHER MEMBER *****
*
***(TESTING)
*
